text: enter the void was good. but it is definitely not for everyone. though the POV wasn't as aggressive. it was the psychedelia and strobbing effects that were very problematic. one of my favorites though.  then there's maniac (remake) a new french extremist remake with elijah wood.  brutal violence can't be well stomached. i even took breaks with that one and I've seen so many violent films. but it helps a lot to feel the sickening and disturbing mind we are going with.  lady in the lake was also great, a film noir that really keeps us at our edge with the paranoia/mystery. ahead of it's time with even a bigger camera in those years. the hold of the camera wasn't well positioned or distanced. but when you see the protagonist looking himself in the, mirror it becomes magical. just like enter the voids face wash scene. you see the eyes blinking, even the towel as it goes around simultaneously with the mirror reflection of our protagonist.  even the current universal soldier took it as inspiration and worked around brainwashing and manipulation of a soldier. and it worked well.  but this looks like a go pro film. cool. but i can't stop imagining the protagonist with the head mount. which is obvious. but for an action film it is insane and it breaks immersion in that aspect.   thought, i can't deny this is amazingly choreographed even not being my cup of tea. the parkour/ stunts has to be respected alone.

text: This is a successful way to make a movie, mark my words. "Revolutionary" is an understatement. Not only can producers save a ton of money by not needing to hire movie stars anymore (you are the main character), it's also an up close and personal view of the action (and gore) that a lot of other movie producers are unwilling to show. This is just the first of it's kind too, the producer said he would like to see what somebody else would do with all the problems he had making this. Imagine a movie shot with something better than a gopro would look like (or a bigger budget). This is going to be an awesome movie! I cant wait to see it, or the next movie like this (this is a money making movie concept, hint hint Steven Spielberg, or any other big producers reading this).
